ystem shall capture a publish or creation reason and stop at an approval boundary until an authorized analytics owner or BI administrator approves the request.\nReturn clarification-required outcomes when required context is missing: The product shall return a clarification-required outcome when required context is missing, including missing dataset reference, metric, chart preview reference, dashboard scope, or publish reason. The clarification response shall identify the missing governed input needed to continue.\nEnforce allowlists and sensitive-dimension restrictions beyond backend RBAC: The product shall enforce dataset, chart, dashboard, and database allowlists and may restrict owner-level, row-level, customer-level, or otherwise sensitive dimensions even when the downstream platform would technically allow access. Governance rules shall take precedence over raw backend reachability.\nLimit backend options to bounded provider controls: The product shall allow backend options only for bounded provider controls such as selected fields, pagination, chart rendering format, or preview output format. Backend options shall not permit arbitrary SQL execution, unbounded export, database switching, allowlist bypass, or hidden publication behavior.\nDeny prohibited raw access and bypass behaviors: The product shall deny requests for raw SQL, raw exports, unrestricted SQL execution, protected database access, dashboard publication bypass, and unapproved saved-query creation. Denial outcomes shall be explicit and audit-friendly.\nProduce audit-friendly records for governed actions, denials, and approvals: The product shall produce audit-friendly outcomes for discovery, bounded answers, previews, approval requests, denials, and clarification stops. Records shall preserve enough context to explain what was requested, what governance boundary applied, and why the system returned the resulting posture.\nRequire real integration evidence before contract generation: Before contract generation, the product definition process shall include real integration evidence for the downstream Superset operations in scope, such as uploaded API documentation, schemas, permission matrices, live discovery, or manually entered operations. The process shall not infer backend operations from project name or domain alone."
      }
    }
  },
